INSERT INTO `history` (`id`, `name`, `description`) VALUES
(1, 'A familiar face', 'On several occasions, you noticed someone following you. You have seen this person many times, but never spoken to them. The few times you tried to approach him, he disappeared. So you wonder what this person wants from you, and why he is following you.'),
(2, 'Abandoned orphan', 'You were abandoned at a very young age and have no idea who your parents are. You lived like a wanderer in the countryside, moving from village to village. You worked on various farms most of your childhood and adolescence.'),
(3, 'Adopted by a different race', 'You never knew who your real parents are and were adopted by a race different from yours. Although you do not look like those who raised you, you have adopted the culture and ways of your adopted race (for example you are a dwarf but you act and think like an elf).'),
(4, 'Adopted child of monks', 'You never knew who your real parents were and had grown up in a monastery, where the monks always treated you adorable. They have become your friends, your teachers, your parents. Now you can\'t wait to see the world.'),
(5, 'Adopted son of a dragon', 'You were raised by a good dragon (or other extremely intelligent and powerful creature) and taught to think like one. You respect dragons for what they are, crafty and intelligent creatures, but you have also learned to avoid, perhaps even fear, evil dragons.'),
(6, 'Adopted son of artisans', 'You never knew your real parents and were raised by your aunt and uncle, who could not have a \'child. They gave you everything a child could dream of having. Yet there is still a void in your life and you would like to know who your biological parents are.'),
(7, 'Adopted son of nobles', 'You were born into the nobility but your mother died giving birth to you, and you never knew your father, who is died at sea when you were very young. So it was your grandfather who raised you, alone. He pampered you and gave you everything, but when he died it was your uncle who inherited all his goods and properties, before forcing you to leave the estate.'),
(8, 'Adopted son of peasants', 'Your parents died when you were still an infant and it was your aunt and uncle, who had many children, who raised you. But most of your \"brothers or sisters\" did everything to make you feel like you weren\'t family. So you are happy to say goodbye and want to prove to them that you are much better than them.'),
(9, 'Amnesia', 'You don\'t know who you are or where you come from. You don\'t even remember your parents and don\'t know if you have brothers or sisters. Your past is a total mystery... that you will discover little by little...'),
(10, 'Ancestral dispute', 'You belong to a rich or noble family that has been in dispute with an important clan over a complicated matter for decades, even centuries. Although you don\'t understand all the details of the case, you grew up hating this feuding family. However, before you do anything drastic, you have decided to get to the bottom of this matter and are now fighting to uncover the truth.'),
(11, 'Animal companion', 'When you were very young, you made friends with an animal. This animal has always been your friend, and you were always there for him as much as he was for you. You would cross an entire continent to protect your mate and members of its species.'),
(12, 'Apprentice carpenter', 'You were trained as a carpenter by your father or someone else in your community. You have learned to build strong structures and know how to use a hammer.'),
(13, 'Apprentice mason', 'You were trained as a mason, by your father or by another person in your community. You have a gift for building things and solving math problems. You may also be stronger than average, from all those years spent in construction.'),
(14, 'Apprentice thief', 'You were raised or trained by one of the biggest pickpockets in the city (according to him) and learned to live among the crowds. So you stole a lot in your youth, and can be proud of it or, on the contrary, ashamed, in which case you could be repentant and devoted to repairing your past sins.'),
(15, 'Banished', 'Your parents were kicked out of their home by their family, and were never allowed to return. Although aware of why they were banned, you strongly believe that they were incorrectly convicted and want to prove their innocence. One day you will clear your parents\' name of all suspicion and allow them to return home'),
(16, 'Big secret', 'Someone dear to you died in your arms. In his last breath, he revealed to you the location of a hidden treasure, which only he knew. Since then, many strangers have followed you, and some might even have tried to capture you. You know they want to know the location of the treasure, and you can\'t get there because you\'d be followed... One day, though, you will.'),
(17, 'Birth prophesied', 'Your birth was predicted and you are destined to do great things. Although you do not yet know what these great things are, you know that one day you will face great adversity, and that your future actions can have a direct impact on the fate of the entire world.'),
(18, 'Birthright', 'A minor artifact was given to you upon the death of your parents. You do not yet know its powers but, like your father and your grandfather before him, you will one day be obliged to use it to fight against Evil. You are not looking forward to this day.'),
(19, 'Blessed by the gods', 'When you were a baby, you survived an accident that should have cost you your life. Since then, the people of your tribe or village are convinced that a god has blessed you and that you are, in one way or another, destined for an exceptional future. You hope not to disappoint them, but suspect that you are nothing special.'),
(20, 'Burnt witch', 'As a child, your mother was accused of vile witchcraft and sentenced to death. She was burned alive before your eyes, but you were too young, too weak and too terrified to intervene. Soon after, you left your house, vowing never to return.'),
(21, 'Child of a famous adventurer', 'You are the child of an adventurer whose name and reputation precede you. However, this is nothing compared to this powerful enemy who seeks revenge on your father, using you as bait.'),
(22, 'Child of a Witch', 'You are the child of an evil witch who has abused you and tormented you to no end. You grew up hating your mother and fearing people like her. When you were older, you ran away from your home. You now wish to never cross paths with your mother again.'),
(23, 'Child of an evil cleric', 'Your father was a cleric of an evil deity, and although he always treated you fairly (at least as much as one can imagine from an evil man), you grew up hating his god and his servants. So you\'re happy to leave home and hope you never see your father or one of his faithful sidekicks again.'),
(24, 'Child of gypsies', 'You grew up in a gypsy clan and have traveled all your life. Although you are now gone, you continue to follow their different traditions and way of life.'),
(25, 'Child of slayers', 'You come from a long line of slayers (demons, dragons, giants, orcs, ...) and your family is renowned for its many exploits. Your ancestors foiled many evil plans in their time, and it is with joy that you continue this family tradition. However, you fear that one day you will pay for all the feats of arms of your family and yours.'),
(26, 'City orphan', 'For as long as you can remember, you have always lived on the streets of a big city. You never knew your parents and have no idea who they were. You are today a resourceful individual who knows every nook and dark alley of this city, in which you grew up.'),
(27, 'Companion of a mythical beast', 'You saved the life of a magical beast. Although you have little control over it, and you may not see each other for weeks or even months, this beast is your best friend and greatest ally.'),
(28, 'Cook', 'You spent your adolescence working as an assistant cook for the local tavern or large inn near your home village, for a major local temple, or for a manor noble. Now you know how to prepare and cook any dish for delicate people who are ready to pay a lot for it.'),
(29, 'Divine favor', 'Long ago, your mother sacrificed her life to help a god or other powerful entity. This entity now considers that it owes a debt to you, as your mother\'s heir. One day he will pay you back.'),
(30, 'Divine parents', 'You are the fruit of the union between a mortal and a god. Although you have inherited few, if any, powers from your divine parent, you feel destined for a better life and perhaps believe that you deserve a place at his side. However, this parent is not very inclined to accept you among their kind, and may even see you as a potential threat.'),
(31, 'Domestic slave', 'You grew up as a slave, working in a noble\'s mansion (cooking, serving food, cleaning, etc). Although you were treated quite well, you are still happy to have been able to buy your freedom and a new life begins for you. Now you want to help other slaves gain their freedom.'),
(32, 'Evil magician\'s assistant', 'Although you may not have the gift, you served a wizard in your youth, and learned many things about magic from him . The man, however, was evil, and made your life such hell that you had to run away. Your experience now naturally causes you to distrust all magicians, and you will have to work to learn to trust one of them.'),
(33, 'Family quest', 'One of your parents was an adventurer. On his deathbed he whispered a name to you that you had never heard before. Ever since, you\'ve been obsessed with finding out what that name means (a person, a place), and you\'ve been trying hard to guess or figure out what your parent wanted you to find with that one clue.'),
(34, 'Famous gladiator', 'As far as you remember, you have always been a gladiator and you delight the crowds. Although you may have been a slave at first, you long ago purchased your freedom, but continue to risk your life fighting for gold, glory, and passion. Your face is known in the city where you used to fight.'),
(35, 'Fisherman', 'You were born by the sea or lake, and were trained in fishing by one of your parents or another person in your community. You know how to sail small boats, guess what the weather will be like tomorrow, and maybe even how to navigate using the stars.'),
(36, 'Former thief', 'You were once a member of a large thieves\' guild. One day you refused to steal an item from the temple of a deity you respect. And, when you later learned that other members of the guild had finally done the job for you, you stole the item in question from them and returned it to its owners. Since that day, you have been on the run.'),
(37, 'Galley slave', 'You were taken from your parents by a band of pirates. For years you were chained and forced to follow the beat of a drum while rowing, rowing and rowing. During a collision, you were one day able to escape. But you have sworn to take revenge on these pirates.'),
(38, 'Gladiator slave', 'You are the child of a slave and grew up in a gladiator school. There you learned how to use exotic weapons and draw enough blood to please the crowd. But although your skills have allowed you to survive thus far, the life of a gladiator is not for you, and so it is fortunate that you have gained your freedom to start a new life.'),
(39, 'Highway robber', 'You were part of a band of highwaymen who attacked caravans and rich nobles as well as peasants. Since then, you have grown up and realized the wrong path you were on. You are now working to correct the mistakes you made during your youth'),
(40, 'Illegitimate child', 'You are the illegitimate child of a local noble, who may or may not be aware of your existence. Because this nobleman never married your mother, you grew up as a commoner and lost his inheritance which, deep in your heart, is rightfully yours.'),
(41, 'Initiate', 'You served as an adept in one of the local temples. While you were being taught the basics of worship, you were gripped by faith. Today you still adhere to this religion and often make offerings to its god.'),
(42, 'Last heir', 'You are the last heir of a noble family that was exterminated by assassins or cut down in a brutal attack or war. Although you lost everyone you loved, you vowed to one day proudly restore your family\'s name. You might even be obsessed with revenge and desperate to find out who is responsible for your family\'s death.'),
(43, 'Librarian', 'In your youth you worked as a librarian for the local temple. You appreciated the calm of life as a librarian and used the opportunity to significantly enrich your knowledge in many areas. But you think you\'re missing out on real life if you continue like this, that\'s why you decided to become an adventurer.'),
(44, 'Lost parent', 'One of your parents (or both, or a brother or sister) has disappeared in a desert region, at sea or in a country distant. When you were old enough to do so, you began searching and this desire to find him fuels every moment of your adventurous life.'),
(45, 'Lumberjack', 'During the winter months of your youth, you worked as a lumberjack. You are comfortable in the forest and rarely get lost there. You know how to handle an ax better than anyone.'),
(46, 'Marked', 'As a child, your family was attacked and you carry the marks of this event with you. Although you don\'t know who was responsible for the attack that killed your parents and scarred your face forever, you remember their crest. One day you will have your revenge.'),
(47, 'Militiaman', 'Before becoming an adventurer, you served as a guard in a city. There you learned the local law, honed your combat skills, and perhaps even arrested a criminal or two, who may have held a grudge against you and may cross your path again one day.'),
(48, 'Mistaken Identity', 'You look like someone who is notoriously famous or infamous (a prince, an evil sorcerer, a sadistic military leader) and, in good or badly, people often treat you as if you were that person. You don\'t know her yet, but one day you will find her.'),
(49, 'Murder in the family', 'Someone in your family has been murdered. The murderer has never been found, but you are driven by the desire to discover the person responsible for this crime and harbor the hope of discovering what his motivation was.'),
(50, 'Orphan of the druidic circle', 'Abandoned in the forest when you were very young, you were adopted by the members of a druidic community. Alongside them, you learned to respect nature and the men and women who dedicate their lives to protecting it. Although you may not have become a Druid, you do what you can to conserve the environment.'),
(51, 'Out of time', 'You do not come from another place, but from another, entirely different era. You were born over 300 years in the future and are familiar with some of the major events currently taking place, events that you considered part of history. Now the story is in front of you, and you are an actor in it. One day, perhaps, you will find a way to return to your time.'),
(52, 'Pact with a devil', 'As a child, your family perished in a fire from which you narrowly escaped. However, during this hell, you prayed and a devil (or other powerful evil creature) answered you. The creature saved you, but in return you promised to do it a great favor later. The day will come when she will remember you, and you are already dreading it.'),
(53, 'Parental debt', 'Your parents owed a large sum to a banker, wealthy landowner, merchant, or nobleman. As they were unable to repay him, they agreed to work for him. However, they are treated unfairly and considered almost like slaves. You have therefore set yourself the goal of recovering enough money to pay off their debt and thus buy back their freedom.'),
(54, 'Political ambition', 'Your family has always played an important political role in your tribe or hometown, perhaps even in the court of a king or queen . You inherited your family\'s ambition and decided to one day replace the current ruler, and you would happily oppose him if he showed signs of weakness or proved unfair or cruel.'),
(55, 'Protected by a thieves guild', 'You were raised and trained by the members of a large thieves guild in a large city. You\'ve learned their trade, committed a lot of petty theft, and may even be wanted by the local authorities. Now you have changed your life, but you know that your past actions or some of your former colleagues could one day cause you serious problems.'),
(56, 'Protected by a tribe of humanoid', 'You were abandoned by your parents and raised by a tribe of orcs, goblins or other similar humanoids ( although you are not of this breed). You have learned to respect them and their ways of life.'),
(57, 'Protector of a sacred place', 'The protector of a sacred place or relic has raised you. Like him, whether he is your parent or your mentor, you played the role of guardian before setting off on your adventure. One day, if this place or relic were in danger, you might be called upon to resume your role as guardian, at least for a while.'),
(58, 'Raised by animals', 'Your parents died in the wild when you were still an infant and an animal or pack (like wolves) raised you. You have developed a special affinity with this breed and have never been comfortable in \"civilized\" places. You may even have problems expressing yourself.'),
(59, 'Revolted', 'When you were a young soldier, you took pity on a man who was condemned to death and disobeyed your lord. You put your life on the line to free this man, because you were convinced of his innocence. The result is that your former lord has offered a reward for your capture and you are now hunted by numerous bounty hunters who have already almost succeeded in capturing you several times.'),
(60, 'Royal heir', 'You are the child and heir of a great leader. One day you will inherit your parent\'s kingdom, but in the meantime you want to prove to the world (and to yourself) that you deserve to be crowned king. You travel in disguise, without bodyguards and without advisors, but with friends and companions.'),
(61, 'Runaway slave', 'You were kidnapped as a child by bandits and sold into slavery. You have then become the property of a rich and evil man who treats his people very badly and forces them to work until exhaustion in his fields. You were able to escape, and you swore to yourself that no one will own you again. But your master wants you back...'),
(62, 'Sacred Mission', 'A high-ranking member of your Church has entrusted you with an important mission. This quest cannot be completed easily or right away. It will take years of research and investigation to uncover the clues that will ultimately lead you to the lost temple or sacred relic you were asked to find.'),
(63, 'Sailor', 'You spent most of your youth serving aboard a merchant ship, noble, or your kingdom\'s navy. You\'re at home at sea, but you\'ve eaten so much fish that you\'ve sworn you\'ll never try it again.'),
(64, 'Sea Rat', 'You are the adopted child of a pirate and his crew. You developed strong bonds with them and mourned when the Royal Navy seized the crew and hanged everyone you knew. Since then, you have distrusted all royal soldiers and the official government.'),
(65, 'Secret heir', 'You were raised by peasants and have lived in the countryside most of your life. But in reality the people who raised you are not your real parents, but the loyal servants of the monarch of your country and you are the child of this monarch and the heir to the kingdom. The problem is you don\'t know it but others do, and a lot of people would pay a lot to see you dead.'),
(66, 'Sent from the past', 'You were born 500 years ago and have, in one way or another, traveled to the future. Instead of looking for a way to return home, you are determined to discover the cause of your family\'s ruin, which, from what you have been able to learn, took place 200 or 300 years ago. Then, perhaps, you will return to your time to change history and thus spare your loved ones.'),
(67, 'Sentenced to death', 'You have been arrested and convicted for a crime that you may or may not have committed. The sentence was death, but you managed to escape before the execution. Now you are on the run and ready to do anything to prove your innocence, even fabricating the evidence.'),
(68, 'Serious handicap', 'You were born with a significant physical handicap, which impairs your strength, dexterity or resistance. Because of this, you walk in a special way and are easily recognized. However, you have learned to cope and have developed other talents. Your aptitude for magic is second to none.'),
(69, 'Servant of nobles', 'You worked for a noble family, tended to their gardens, cleaned their manor or castle, served their meals, and/or repaired their buildings. You know when to smile politely, say “yes sir” and look away.'),
(70, 'Severe past', 'You did serious things when you were younger, perhaps murder. You have since completely changed your way of being and now dedicate your life to the search for truth, justice and the protection of the innocent. However, no matter what you do, you know that what you did will one day come back to haunt you.'),
(71, 'Sewer Rat', 'You grew up in the sewers of a big city. Its maze-like basements have been your only home. But although poor, dirty and poorly dressed, life was not so bad for you, until you decided to come to the surface.'),
(72, 'Slum Society', 'You come from a secret underground society that inhabits the sewers of a major city. The people around you, although generous, live in poverty and are considered a scourge and a shame by the other residents of the town. In fact, they are not even recognized, let alone protected, by local law. Deep in your heart, you know that they deserve a better fate and wish you could do something concrete to change their destiny.'),
(73, 'Soldier of the king', 'From a young age you were trained as a soldier and had served the rulers of your kingdom in their personal guard. You have fought in various battles, perhaps even participated in wars. Either way, they were traumatic experiences that may have hardened your heart against violence, or put you on the path to peace.'),
(74, 'Son of a caravan driver', 'You are the child of a merchant who owns a caravan or of someone who works for such a person (a guard, a cart driver). In your youth, you visited many places and knew half the world. Now you want to see some of these places again.'),
(75, 'Son of a knight', 'You are the child of a knight who swore loyalty to one of the local leaders. You may even be the descendant of a long line of knights and you are willing to do anything to continue in this proud tradition.'),
(76, 'Son of a magician', 'You are the child of a magician and are always at home in libraries and laboratories. Although you may not have developed the ability to wield magical forces as much as your father, you have still learned many complex things related to this inscrutable art.'),
(77, 'Son of a mercenary', 'You are the child of a mercenary, and as a young man you visited many strange places. You never had a home, but your parents always gave you what you needed. You have had a taste for travel since your youth.'),
(78, 'Son of a merchant', 'You are the child of a merchant who owns a modest but successful workshop in a small or large town. You are comfortable in urban environments, but know almost nothing about nature and its way of life. Like your parents, you are probably a charismatic individual who prefers to avoid dark forests and uncivilized mountains.'),
(79, 'Son of a peasant', 'You are the child of a peasant, free or serf, and live on a farm. You are curious about what the world is really like beyond the community you grew up in, and fascinated by the wonderful things you discover on your adventures.'),
(80, 'Son of a Pirate', 'You are the child of an infamous pirate or one of his lesser-known henchmen. You have lived aboard a boat all your life and are very comfortable at sea. Although you may not have followed your father\'s path, you still respect his \'profession\' (it takes courage to be a pirate) and don\'t see piracy as something that needs to be eradicated.'),
(81, 'Son of a priest', 'You are the child of a clergyman and the local temple has always been your home. Although you may not be as devoted as your parents, you still possess a deep respect for their divinity.'),
(82, 'Son of a troubadour', 'You are the child of artists (acrobats, poets, musicians, actors) and have traveled all your life, never staying long at the same location. Like your parents, you feel at home anywhere and make friends very easily.'),
(83, 'Son of a warrior', 'You are the child of a warrior who likely served in your hometown\'s militia or as a guard for a noble. You have admired your father all your life. He was the inspiration that led you to become an adventurer.'),
(84, 'Son of an artisan', 'You are the child of an artisan and live in a small or large town. From a young age, you were naturally trained in the footsteps of your father. But you ultimately decided that his profession, although noble, was not for you.'),
(85, 'Son of barbarians', 'You come from a barbarian tribe and have inherited its traditions and ways of doing things, which many often do not understand. You are proud of this heritage and ardently defend the customs and way of life of your people.'),
(86, 'Son of landowners', 'You are the child of rather wealthy landowners and know that you will inherit these properties one day. In the meantime, you have set out to prove to everyone that your family is worthy of being recognized as noble (or at least of moving up the social ladder).'),
(87, 'Son of nobles', 'You are the child of nobles and very proud of your family, its history and what it represents. You became an adventurer to make your parents proud of you and prove to them that you are worthy of their noble heritage.'),
(88, 'Squire', 'Even if you are not necessarily of noble blood or the son of a knight, you served under the orders of a knight in your youth. There you learned to honor chivalrous virtues, even if you did not subsequently follow the path to knighthood.'),
(89, 'Stable boy', 'In your youth, you worked in the stables of a popular inn, the militia of your hometown or a castle in nobles. You are comfortable with horses, enjoy looking after them, and are probably a skilled rider.'),
(90, 'Stolen heirloom', 'You belong to an old family that has lost its most cherished symbol or talisman (an amulet, a bracelet, a royal crown, a great sword, a mithral breastplate, an old ring, a wooden totem, etc.). This undoubtedly magical heirloom was in your family for generations before someone stole it. You then swore in front of your entire family to find the stolen inheritance.'),
(91, 'Strange birthmark', 'You were born with a strange birthmark of a very particular shape (eye, tree, bear paw, dragon, etc.) . You know that mark must mean something, because a lot of people tell you to hide it. So you don\'t know its meaning, but you are determined to find out.'),
(92, 'Temple Guard', 'You spent your adolescence guarding one of your community\'s local temples. There you learned to respect the cult you served or, on the contrary, you realized that this god and his clergy were a bunch of liars and thieves who did not deserve your respect.'),
(93, 'The foreign child', 'You are a native of a very distant country, and had the misfortune one day to pass through a magical portal which teleported you where you you find now. So you have become an adventurer almost out of obligation, and your goal is to find a way to return home.'),
(94, 'The sins of the father', 'You are the child of a man who was condemned to death. For some reason, the authorities who executed him are now looking for you. Perhaps they believe you know something that could endanger or harm them, or they simply want to exterminate your entire family. Either way, the fact is that they are chasing you.'),
(95, 'Thug', 'As a child, you were part of a gang of thugs in the town where you grew up. You survived thanks to your fists and still think today that the strongest wolf is the one who must lead the pack. Although you now regret the crimes you committed, you are still a boorish and intimidating individual.'),
(96, 'Trapper, hunter', 'You were trained as a trapper or hunter. You are at home in nature, you know how to use a rope, and have learned a thing or two about animal life, which you admire and respect.'),
(97, 'Unjustly accused', 'When you were younger, you were accused of a heinous crime. And although you were declared innocent, people in your hometown still treated you like you were a criminal. You then convinced yourself that you would never be well seen there, and left the city, vowing never to return.'),
(98, 'Unknown parents', 'You have not known your real parents and everyone around you refuses to talk to you about them. From evasive comments and whispered conversations, the only thing you learned was that they were notoriously feared. One day you might learn why.'),
(99, 'Waiter', 'You worked as a waiter in the local tavern or for a large inn near your home village. There you learned to always keep your ears open, and more importantly, to always keep your mouth closed. You\'re probably good at getting information.'),
(100, 'Wild child', 'You grew up in a cave on the side of a hill or in an abandoned cabin in the woods, with your mother who the surrounding population considers to be a witch . Nature is your home, but good manners and social relations are foreign to you.');
INSERT INTO `creature_type` (`id`, `name`, `description`) VALUES
(1, 'Aberration', 'Aberrations are utterly alien beings. Many of them have innate magical abilities drawn from the creature’s alien mind rather than the mystical forces of the world. The quintessential aberrations are aboleths, beholders, mind flayers, and slaadi.'),
(2, 'Beast', 'Beasts are nonhumanoid creatures that are a natural part of the fantasy ecology. Some of them have magical powers, but most are unintelligent and lack any society or language. Beasts include all varieties of ordinary animals, dinosaurs, and giant versions of animals.'),
(3, 'Celestial', 'Celestials are creatures native to the Upper Planes. Many of them are the servants of deities, employed as messengers or agents in the mortal realm and throughout the planes. Celestials are good by nature, so the exceptional celestial who strays from a good alignment is a horrifying rarity. Celestials include angels, couatls, and pegasi.'),
(4, 'Construct', 'Constructs are made, not born. Some are programmed by their creators to follow a simple set of instructions, while others are imbued with sentience and capable of independent thought. Golems are the iconic constructs. Many creatures native to the outer plane of Mechanus, such as modrons, are constructs shaped from the raw material of the plane by the will of more powerful creatures.'),
(5, 'Dragon', 'Dragons are large reptilian creatures of ancient origin and tremendous power. True dragons, including the good metallic dragons and the evil chromatic dragons, are highly intelligent and have innate magic. Also in this category are creatures distantly related to true dragons, but less powerful, less intelligent, and less magical, such as wyverns and pseudodragons.'),
(6, 'Elemental', 'Elementals are creatures native to the elemental planes. Some creatures of this type are little more than animate masses of their respective elements, including the creatures simply called elementals. Others have biological forms infused with elemental energy. The races of genies, including djinn and efreet, form the most important civilizations on the elemental planes. Other elemental creatures include azers, invisible stalkers, and water weirds.'),
(7, 'Fey', 'Fey are magical creatures closely tied to the forces of nature. They dwell in twilight groves and misty forests. In some worlds, they are closely tied to the Feywild, also called the Plane of Faerie. Some are also found in the Outer Planes, particularly the planes of Arborea and  the Beastlands. Fey include dryads, pixies, and satyrs.'),
(8, 'Fiend', 'Fiends are creatures of wickedness that are native to the Lower Planes. A few are the servants of deities, but many more labor under the leadership of archdevils and demon princes. Evil priests and mages sometimes summon fiends to the material world to do their bidding. If an evil celestial is a rarity, a good fiend is almost inconceivable. Fiends include demons, devils, hell hounds, rakshasas, and yugoloths.'),
(9, 'Giant', 'Giants tower over humans and their kind. They are humanlike in shape, though some have multiple heads (ettins) or deformities (fomorians). The six varieties of true giant are hill giants, stone giants, frost giants, fire giants, cloud giants, and storm giants. Besides these, creatures such as ogres and trolls are giants.'),
(10, 'Humanoid', 'Humanoids are the main peoples of the D&D world, both civilized and savage, including humans and a tremendous variety of other species. They have language and culture, few if any innate magical abilities (though most humanoids can learn spellcasting), and a bipedal  form. The most common humanoid races are the ones most suitable as player characters: humans, dwarves, elves, and halflings. Almost as numerous but far more savage and brutal, and almost uniformly evil, are the races of goblinoids (goblins, hobgoblins, and bugbears), orcs, gnolls, lizardfolk, and kobolds.'),
(11, 'Monstrosity', 'Monstrosities are monsters in the strictest sense-frightening creatures that are not ordinary, not truly natural, and almost never benign. Some are the results of magical experimentation gone awry (such as owlbears), and others are the product of terrible curses (including minotaurs and yuan-ti). They defy categorization, and in some sense serve as a catch-all category for creatures that don’t fit into any other type.'),
(12, 'Ooze', 'Oozes are gelatinous creatures that rarely have a fixed shape. They are mostly subterranean, dwelling in caves and dungeons and feeding on refuse, carrion, or creatures unlucky enough to get in their way. Black puddings and gelatinous cubes are among the most recognizable oozes.'),
(13, 'Plant', 'Plants in this context are vegetable creatures, not ordinary flora. Most of them are ambulatory, and some are carnivorous. The quintessential plants are the shambling mound and the treant. Fungal creatures such as the gas spore and the myconid also fall into this category.'),
(14, 'swarm of Tiny Beasts', 'The swarms presented here aren\'t ordinary or benign assemblies of little creatures. They form as a result of some sinister or unwholesome influence. A vampire can summon swarms of bats and rats from the darkest corners of the night, while the very presence of a mummy lord can cause scarab beetles to boil up from the sand-filled depths of its tomb. A hag might have the power to turn swarms of ravens against her enemies, while a yuan-ti abomination might have swarms of poisonous snakes slithering in its wake. Even druids can\'t charm these swarms, and their aggressiveness is borderline unnatural.'),
(15, 'Undead', 'Undead are once-living creatures brought to a horrifying state of undeath through the practice of necromantic magic or some unholy curse. Undead include walking corpses, such as vampires and zombies, as well as bodiless spirits, such as ghosts and specters.');
