(5, 3, 3, 'Unlocking an ancient mystery is worth the price of a civilization.'),
(5, 3, 4, 'I overlook obvious solutions in favor of complicated ones.'),
(5, 3, 5, 'I speak without really thinking through my words, invariably insulting others.'),
(5, 3, 6, 'I can\'t keep a secret to save my life, or anyone else\'s.'),
(5, 4, 1, 'Knowledge. The path to power and self-improvement is through knowledge. (Neutral)'),
(5, 4, 2, 'Beauty. What is beautiful points us beyond itself toward what is true. (Good)'),
(5, 4, 3, 'Logic. Emotions must not cloud our logical thinking. (lawful)'),
(5, 4, 4, 'No Limits. Nothing should fetter the infinite possibility inherent in all existence. (Chaotic)'),
(5, 4, 5, 'Power. Knowledge is the path to power and domination. (Evil)'),
(5, 4, 6, 'Self Improvement. The goal of a life of study is the betterment of oneself. (Any)'),
(5, 5, 1, 'I use polysyllabic words that convey the impression of great erudition.'),
(5, 5, 2, 'I\'ve read every book in the world\'s greatest libraries - or I like to boast that I have.'),
(5, 5, 3, 'I\'m used to helping out those who aren\'t as smart as I am, and I patiently explain anything and everything to others.'),
(5, 5, 4, 'There\'s nothing I like more than a good mystery.'),
(5, 5, 5, 'I\'m willing to listen to every side of an argument before I make my own judgment.'),
(5, 5, 6, 'I ... speak ... slowly ... when talking to idiots, ... which ... almost ... everyone ... is compared ... to me.'),
(5, 5, 7, 'I am horribly, horribly awkward in social situations.'),
