<p>For the Player profile, rights are refined according to whether or not a player has been selected and is involved in a quest.</p>', 'See access rights', 'access_right.png', 0, 12),
(202, 'Action buttons', 'bi-grid', 'Manage the action buttons', 'Manage the action buttons', '', '<p>This function, reserved for administrators, allows you to define the set of buttons to be displayed according to an object\'s status, and to link these buttons to object classes.</p>\r\r\
<p>These buttons may behave differently if they are displayed in a table row, or if they are displayed when editing a record.</p>', 'See action buttons', 'action-buttons.png', 0, 13),
(300, 'Classes', 'bi-heart', 'List of the available character classes within the game', 'Available classes', '', '<p>Classes define a character\'s role, abilities, and worldview. A fighter, for example, is a skilled warrior focused on combat, while a cleric is a spellcaster aligned with a divine power.</p>\r\r\
<p>As characters level up, they gain new abilities and improve existing ones. Multiclassing allows characters to combine aspects of different classes, creating unique and versatile builds. The four core classes—fighter, wizard, rogue, and cleric—are foundational to most campaigns.</p>', 'See available classes', 'classes.png', 0, 50),
(400, 'Images', 'bi-image', 'List of the available images for race\'s class and gender within the game', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 800),
(500, 'Items', 'bi-backpack2', 'List of the available items within the game sorted by item types', 'Available items', '', '<p>Armor is crucial for protection, but heavier armor can restrict movement. Proficiency in armor is essential for effective use, and the armor\'s weight can affect a character\'s speed.</p>\r\r\
<p>Weapons are categorized as melee or ranged, and proficiency in different weapon types is determined by class, race, and feats. Weapons can have special properties like ammunition or magical effects.</p>\r\r\
<p>Tools are used for various tasks, such as crafting, repairing, or picking locks. Proficiency with tools allows characters to add their proficiency bonus to ability checks related to those tools.</p>', 'See available items', 'items.png', 0, 54),
(800, 'Player administration', 'bi-person-gear', 'Manage every players', 'Player administration', NULL, '<p>As an admin, you can validate, delete ou restore any player</p>\r\r\
<p>You din\'t need to be the player\'s owner to manage them</p>', 'Player admin', 'players.png', 0, 100),
(802, 'Players', 'bi-controller', 'List of created players', 'Manage your players', '', '<p>Access a list of your players. Manage their status, consult their characteristics.</p>\r\r\
<p>The player is the central part of the game. They are your personification, and other players only see you through these characters.</p>\r\r\
<p>Choose them with care, as their characteristics will help you successfully complete your quests.</p>', 'Manage players', 'players.png', 0, 101),
(900, 'Player Builder', 'bi-tools', 'A wizard to create new characters', 'Create a new player', '', '<p>To create a D&D character, you\'ll first need to choose a race, such as a human, elf, dwarf, or halfling. This choice determines your character\'s physical attributes and innate abilities. Next, select a class, like a fighter, wizard, rogue, or cleric. This defines your character\'s role in the game, their skills, and their combat abilities. After that, you\'ll assign numerical values to six ability scores: Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma. These scores will influence your character\'s performance in various tasks. Finally, you\'ll flesh out your character\'s backstory, personality, and physical appearance, bringing them to life and making them unique.</p>', 'New player', 'builder.png', 0, 102),
(1004, 'Shop', 'bi-shop', 'A shop were you can buy armors, weapon and other stuff', 'Go for shopping', '', '<p>The vibrant marketplaces of cities offer a wide range of goods, from everyday items to exotic treasures. For adventurers, acquiring suitable equipment is essential for survival.</p>\r\r\
<p>When creating a character, players can either choose from a set of starting equipment based on their class and background, or they can start with a specific amount of gold to purchase items from the marketplace. The choice of starting equipment can reflect the character\'s backstory and personality.</p>', 'Go for shopping', 'shop.png', 0, 106),
(1100, 'Possessions', 'bi-safe', 'Here\'s everything your player owns. It\'s up to you to choose what to take with you on your next adventure.', 'Pick up items from your treasure trove', '', '<p>You\'ve been on quite the journey, haven\'t you? Along the way, you\'ve gathered a whole bunch of amazing objects, gems, and magical items.</p>\r\r\
<p>So, before you set off on your next exciting adventure, take a moment to look through your treasure trove and choose the items that will help you successfully complete another quest.</p>', 'See your possessions', 'belongings.png', 0, 104),
(1204, 'Quests', 'bi-play-btn', 'Resuming the quest where it left off', 'Resume your quest', NULL, NULL, 'Resume quest', NULL, 1, 210),
(1300, 'Races', 'bi-people', 'List of available races within the game', 'Available races', '', '<p>The worlds of Dungeons & Dragons are teeming with diverse and fascinating races. From the common humans to the exotic dragonborn and drow, each race brings unique abilities and cultural nuances to the game. Cities like Waterdeep and Sigil are melting pots of cultures, where different races coexist and interact.</p>\r\r\
<p>When creating a character, players must choose a race that aligns with their desired playstyle. Humans, dwarves, elves, and halflings are popular choices due to their versatility and common representation in adventuring parties. However, other races like gnomes, half-orcs, and tieflings offer unique abilities and backstories. Each race has distinct physical traits, cultural norms, and alignment tendencies, providing players with a rich foundation for character development.</p>', 'See available race', 'races.png', 0, 51),
(1402, 'Rules', 'bi-diagram-3', 'List of rules used by the inference rule engine of the game', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 810),
(1600, 'Spells', 'bi-magic', 'List of the available spells within the game', 'Available spells', '', '<p>Spells are magical effects that can be cast by various classes and creatures. They range from simple cantrips to powerful high-level spells.</p>\r\r\
<p>Spellcasters must know or prepare spells before casting them, and they have a limited number of spell slots to use each day. Casting a spell at a higher level than its normal level can increase its power. Ritual spells are special spells that can be cast over a longer period without expending a spell slot.</p>', 'See available spells', 'spells.png', 0, 55),
(1702, 'Stories', 'bi-book', 'List of available stories', 'Available stories', '', '<p>There\'s nothing more rewarding than creating adventures as a Dungeon Master! It\'s so much fun! You get to design the most imaginative worlds, encounters, and storylines. While there\'s no one right way to define an adventure, it often begins with an intriguing hook, like a rumor or a quest. This hook is like a little invitation to the players, drawing them gently into the adventure and leading them to a series of encounters. These encounters can be tied together by location, theme, or a specific event, which helps to create a nice, cohesive narrative. The goal is to create experiences that are really engaging for the players and that they\'ll love!</p>\r\r\
<p>We\'ve put together a list of stories that we think you\'ll love!</p>', 'See stories', 'Story.png', 0, 200),
(1801, 'Users', 'bi-person-vcard', 'List of defined users within the game', 'Manage the users', 'List of defined users within the game', '<p>This function, reserved for administrators, is used to manage users. A dashboard allows an administrator to force validation of a user in the event of a problem receiving the e-mail confirming the user\'s e-mail address, or to invalidate an indelicate user.</p>\r\r\
<p>It can also be used to give administrator or designer privileges to known users.</p>\r\r\
<p>This function only manages data that is strictly necessary for the application to function properly.</p>', 'Manage the users', 'users.png', 0, 10),
(1900, 'User activities', 'bi-person-workspace', 'List of the logins and logouts of the user in the game', 'Monitor the users activity', '', '<p>This function, reserved for administrators, allows you to track user activity by capturing login and logout dates.</p>\r\r\
<p>In the interests of privacy, this function does not allow us to know what users are doing in the application. In particular, it does not allow us to know the content of messages exchanged during a quest.</p>', 'See users activity', 'user-activity.png', 0, 11);

